==English==
===Etymology===
German, from [[Entscheidung]] ‘decision’.

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /ɛnt'ʃʌɪdʊŋsˌpɹɒbləm/

===Noun===
'''Entscheidungsproblem'''
# ''(Maths, Logic)'' a [[decision]] problem, of finding a way to decide whether a formula is true or provable within a given system
#:*'''1999''': ‘The '''''Entscheidungsproblem''''',’ Rudy said.  ‘Meaning?’  Alan explained, ‘Hilbert wanted to know whether any given statement could, in principle, be found true or false.’ — Neal Stephenson, ''Cryptonomicon''